paragraph_text: Arden Building Maintenance have won the contract at Geelong Performing Arts Centre. Arden has already begun work, completing the Band of Hope Building and installing a new Welsh Slate roof.
Arden Building Maintenance has recently installed a new prototype kiosk style shop for Foxtel overnight at Chadstone Shopping Centre, with its new eye catching look and inter active screens.

Arden Building Maintetance recently refurbished the slate roof at Albert Park Primary School. It was a complex roof replacement in Welsh slate under Heritage Victoria. Arden Building Maintenance and Albert Park Primary School are both very happy with the final result.

Arden completed a relaunch for Woolworths Woodvale. The job involved not only the main part of the store but also in the back area. This job was completed on time and budget with the client very happy. Great work Arden!

Arden completed an office refurbishment of Managers office and Kitchenette. It was a 4 week program upgrading walls, floors, ceiling, Air conditioning and Lighting, data and power. The job also involved new fixtures supplied and installed. Arden completed the job on time and on budget.
Arden is adept at providing a range of trades for maintenance purposes including plumbing, electrical, carpentry, mechanical services and shop fitting.
Arden has 12 + years’ experience in working with clients to maintain their commercial facilities according to a time frame and budget that meets their core business needs.

Arden Group has a huge amount of experience in the fit out and refurbishment of commercial spaces. For over 12 years we have become experts in planning ahead and often executing works out of normal hours in order to achieve client aims with minimal disruption to their regular trading.

Arden Group can assist in the concept, design, fit out and ongoing maintenance of almost any commercial facility.  The company has a broad experience in all areas of commercial construction as well as the staff, subcontractors and other resources required to complete the job on time and on budget.

Arden provides Facilities Management services to a range of trusted clients throughout Australia. Our expertise in this field lies mainly with Universities & Schools.
The Arden group is a Building & Maintenance services company with expertise in a wide range of areas.
Arden aims to provide clients with a diverse range of services and build strong relationships so that all of their needs can be met through a single point of contact.
From project conception through to project management and ongoing maintenance, Arden is here to make your building concepts a reality.
To provide our customers with a comprehensive range of building services of the highest possible standard and quality.
– Creating a culture that can take on any challenge;
– Creating a safe and healthy work environment
– Delivering Value and ensuring equity and fairness in pricing;
– Acting in an ethical Manner at all times;
– Building long-term relationships with our Customers;
– Developing staff and contractors skills and expertise.

Arden had the privelege of working with renowned New Zealand sculptor Phil Price to install one of his creations at La Trobe University.  Entitled “Chrysalid” and standing 11 metres high, the piece has several moving parts and was assembled using a crane and knuckle boom.  Arden prepared all of the structural steel and footings in the lead up to assembly day and was also lucky to have some good weather during the more difficult stages.
After some pretty heavy winds Arden Building Maintenance had quite the clean up at Monash University.

Alan began his career as a Property Manager for a CBD Real Estate Company in 1974 and also completed Business Studies and Building Techniques at RMIT University during this period. In 1996, the attraction to being involved in all facets of Commercial Buildings and their Maintenance motivated Alan to run his own Building and Maintenance Business for 8 years until founding Arden in conjunction with Richard Pitcher in 2002. Alan holds an unlimited Commercial Builders Licence in Victoria with mutual recognition in all States of Australia as well as a diploma in OH&S.

Richard began his career in the building industry as a plumber and holds a Plumbing Licence and a Residential Builders (Vic) licence. Prior to the formation of Arden in 2002, Richard successfully ran his own Plumbing business for 12 years and has never forgotten the hands on experience he gained throughout this period. Richard is highly energetic and focused on developing the services Arden provides.
Glenn Welsh – OHS&E and QA Manager
Arden completed a refurbishment at BWS Dianella. This job was completed by our WA team with our client very happy. Ready for the opening on 28/09/18. Great work!

The Arden team in WA have just completed the fit out of Coles Express Myaree.
Arden recently completed the repair of a canopy at the 7 Eleven store in Easter Creek NSW
Arden Building Maintenance tidied up the mess at Coles Express Hastings after a Ram Raid.
Arden has recently completed the entire fit-out of the Coles Express service station in Gympie.
Arden’s team in Queensland has re-built the Caltex Bundaberg office. Great result.
Arden have just installed a fully functional foodbench for the Coles Supermarket / Coles Express showcase at the Melbourne Exhibition Centre

Arden were invited to the grand opening of the brand new Coles Express Campbellfield store. Arden had just completed the fit out of this store. A huge thank you to all our Arden staff who participated in the fit out, job well done.

The Arden Team have just completed a Major refurbishment of the BP Coomera Travel Centre. These works included New Truckers Facilities, a facelift of the food court, new public amenities, a refresh and replacement of BP signage and Canopy livery, a new and improved Convenience store and Wild Bean Cafe.

Arden have just finished the new storage facility at Coles Express Cotham Rd Kew. Arden have also completed major internal store works and an upgrade to the managers office. The Coles Express staff were delighted.

Arden have recently completed the online fit out of Coles Churchill. Racking was cleared and relocated, cool-room wall built, installation of roller door and emergency door, all desk and shelving supplied and install and all line marking was completed by Arden.
The Arden team in WA have just completed the full fit out of the Coles Bakeries in Wanneroo and Swan View.
Arden QLD have just completed a canopy repair at 7 Eleven Murarrie. The canopy was hit by a truck and needed urgent repairs.
Arden provides Facilities Management services to a range of trusted clients throughout Australia. Our expertise in this field lies mainly with Universities & Schools.
The Arden Team in South Australia have just completed repairs on the Coles Express Darlington Store. Repairs were required after a car accident on site.
Arden have just completed the removal of all tiles in the sales area and re-tiling of the same area for Puma Petroleum in Tugan on the Gold Coast.
Arden Building have just completed the shop fit out of Reid Cycles in South Australia. A great result.

Store Flooded over the Christmas period in 2017. Arden Building engaged to make safe and clean site for hand over to Viva Energy. Arden were then engaged by Coles to rebuilt and refit the store internals and to improve the livery of the external building incorporating their Big and Bold over a 4 week period in April 2018.
Arden completed a Click and Collect install in Wagga Wagga. The job involved line marking and painting as well as door and signage installation. The work was completed on time and on budget.

Coles Springvale Bakery got a full transformation by the Arden team. Complete demolition of existing bakery, extension of floor, removal of ceiling, complete new solid ceiling, new tiles to all walls, complete new epoxy floor, new plumbing, and installation of new electrical sub-board, new outlets for equipment, relocation and extension of fire services, relocation of mechanical services, modification to roof top fans for extraction purposes, supply all new stainless steel benches and bump rails. Great work team!
Arden completed a Click and Collect install in Waurn Ponds. The job involved line marking and painting as well as door and signage installation. The work was completed on time and on budget.
Arden has successfully completed another bakery refurbishment. The job was completed on time and on budget for a happy client. Great job team!

Another challenging remote project for the Arden team in Tom Price WA, while keeping the store trading the team managed to bring this store up to current spec. The works included but weren’t limited to changing to the entry door to an automatic sliding door, full electrical strip out and re wire, service counter move, server move, full painting scope, signage upgrade and relay of all fixtures. Not one incident and works finished ahead of schedule. Onto the next one.
Arden completed a fit out of new Viva/Coles Express Truckstop in the northern suburbs of Brisbane. It was a three week program and was finished on time and in budget. Great work!
Arden successfully located and repaired water leak in forecourt.
The Arden team in WA have just completed a refresh at Caltex Belmont.
Arden have just completed the full fit out of the Coles Express store in Park Holme South Australia. Coles Express were very happy with the finished product.
The Arden Team soldiered on through harsh weather conditions earlier this week at the Coles in Kingston (Tasmania)
Arden have just completed the Coles Somerville Renewal.

Store Flooded over the Christmas period in 2017. Arden Building engaged to make safe and clean site for hand over to Viva Energy. Arden were then engaged by Coles to rebuilt and refit the store internals and to improve the livery of the external building incorporating their Big and Bold over a 4 week period in April 2018.

We were contracted by Southern Volkswagen car dealership to remove current PA door , concrete kerbing  and slab. We also had to create the opening install a concrete cross over supply and install necessary flashings. Great Work Arden!
Arden Building engaged to supply and install all items to fit out internals of their first Truck Stop in Queensland and brand external elements over a 2 month period from April to May 2018.
Arden just completed a new BWS store in Mandurah Forum. Job was completed all on time and on budget. Great work!

Arden have completed stage 1 at Sunshine Developmental School included refurbishment works to upgrade the well being block and Central classroom block. The works included upgrades to the toilet facilities and accessible toilets that featured hoist lifting equipment to aid disabled students. The building works provide an improved use of space with open areas and sliding wall features, providing adaptable classrooms that are often required at Sunshine Developmental School. The existing buildings also required some much needed maintenance and repairs to bring it in line with today’s standards and refurbishment will be a great improvement for all the staff and students
Arden has completed a Reset 5.0 job at Eltham Liquor Land which involved  external signage and new alucobond to bulkhead above fridge doors/ceiling painting/wall painting/electrical works.
